---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Harry Sivasambu"
  description="Cloud engineer portfolio, projects, and writing."
>
  <section id="about" class="card" style="padding: 22px;">
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--muted);">
      Hi, I'm Harry, a Technical Project Manager from Toronto, Canada who stays current by building, shipping, and learning in public.
      I lead teams with clarity, unblock delivery, and turn complex technology into outcomes teams can trust.
    </p>
    <p style="margin: 10px 0 0; color: var(--muted);">
      I also love the NBA, Formula 1, travelling the world, and hunting down the best local street food in every
      city I visit.
    </p>
    <p style="margin: 10px 0 0; color: var(--muted);">
      Explore the projects and posts below to see how I work, what I learn, and how I keep pace with modern platforms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="projects" style="margin-top: 18px;">
    <h2 style="margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 22px;">Featured Projects</h2>

    <div class="grid" style="display: grid; gap: 12px; grid-template-columns: repeat(12, minmax(0, 1fr));">
      <div class="card" style="grid-column: span 6;">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 6px;">Cloud Resume Challenge</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--muted);">
          Imported a production-style AWS stack into Terraform, validated zero-drift, and automated deploys.
        </p>
        <a href="/blog/cloud-resume-challenge">Read write-up →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="grid-column: span 6;">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 6px;">Portfolio + Blog</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--muted);">
          Python, web design, AWS, and much more.
        </p>
        <a href="/blog">Browse posts →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="technical-writing" style="margin-top: 18px;">
    <h2 style="margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 22px;">Technical Deep Dives</h2>
    <p style="margin: 0 0 14px; color: var(--muted);">
      Technical deep dives exploring system design, cloud architecture, and emerging AI concepts?written to document how I reason about tradeoffs, constraints, and real-world engineering decisions.
    </p>

    <div class="grid" style="display: grid; gap: 12px; grid-template-columns: repeat(12, minmax(0, 1fr));">
      <div class="card" style="grid-column: span 4;">
        <span class="pill">System Design</span>
        <h3 style="margin: 10px 0 6px;">Resilient Event Pipelines</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--muted);">
          Designing for backpressure, retries, and graceful degradation in high-throughput systems.
        </p>
        <a href="/technical-writing">Read Article</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="grid-column: span 4;">
        <span class="pill">AI Developments</span>
        <h3 style="margin: 10px 0 6px;">Human-in-the-Loop Guardrails</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--muted);">
          Mapping where AI helps, where it harms, and how to design reliable review loops.
        </p>
        <a href="/technical-writing">Read Article</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="grid-column: span 4;">
        <span class="pill">Financial Literacy</span>
        <h3 style="margin: 10px 0 6px;">Finance Basics for Builders</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--muted);">
          Translating cash flow, runway, and unit economics into product decisions.
        </p>
        <a href="/technical-writing">Read Article</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="contact" style="margin-top: 18px;">
    <h2 style="margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 22px;">Contact</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul style="margin: 10px 0 0; padding-left: 18px;">
        <li><a href="https://github.com/hsivasambu">Github</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/hsivasambu/">LinkedIn</a></li>
        <li><a href="mailto:h.sivasambu@gmail.com">Email</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

